title: For Sale:  Texas Ranger 22 Single Action BOX/TAG/PAPERS MINT!
postcontent: This is a piece of 1980s history. Still in the box, with the original hang-tag and manual and whatever came in the box. The single action 22 is several grades above the usual ones from FIE, which are pretty decent. This one is put together much better and has a solid feel and is quite heavy as the barrels on a 22 have a lot of steel. Check the cylinder as the rear has a recessed rim so there is no gap and the rear is what appears to be stainless that was left bare. I am not sure, but going by how it looks the cylinder or part of it is stainless. The button for releasing the cylinder rod and the other screws are gold and the grips wood. The gun has been fired as I see a line on the cylinder from rotation but I did not fire it as it just looks too clean and perfect in its box. The hammer clicks back nicely into the positions, the loading gate lets you drop one in at a time and pop them out with the ejector when finished. It does have a hammer block safety but still, best not to carry with a loaded round under the hammer. I sold the base model single action in so-so shape for $135 and this one is in mint/perfect condition AND has the box and papers AND most importamt.....this is a MUCH nicer gun. While the cheaper ones are great truck, camping or boat guns, this is one you do not want to bang up. These nicer grade FIEs do sell for more. The regular 25acp GT27 is a 100 dollar gun but the Tigress model in a similar box with the papers and upgrades all over is selling for double that.
